Global Infrared Temperature Measurement Modules Market Insights
Infrared Temperature Measurement Modules Market size was valued at USD 2.1 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 3.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Infrared Temperature Measurement Modules Market Overview
The global infrared temperature measurement modules market is projected to grow significantly over the next decade. The market size reached USD 1.45 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 8.6%, reaching an estimated value of USD 3.45 billion by 2034. This growth is driven by increased demand in industrial applications such as process monitoring, predictive maintenance, and quality control. Additionally, the expansion of the consumer electronics sector and advancements in automotive and healthcare industries contribute to the market's expansion. With the rise of automation and IoT technologies, infrared temperature measurement modules are increasingly being used for precise, non-contact temperature measurement in various industries.

